President Barack Obama expressed his condolences on the passing of President John Evans Atta Mills of Ghana. He remembered his visit to Ghana in 2009 and the warm hospitality he received from President Mills and the Ghanaian people. President Mills was recognized for his efforts in improving the lives of Ghanaians and promoting economic growth despite global challenges. He also emphasized the deepening partnership between the United States and Ghana in areas such as good governance, economic development, human rights, and fair treatment for all Ghanaians. President Obama offered his deepest condolences to the people of Ghana and highlighted the enduring bonds between their democracies that President Mills helped strengthen.